<br>
This is a distinctly PoP phenomenon. I am a good puller, its been one of the skills I took pride in. I started doing it on Orc Hill in Gfay, and kept it up right up to PoP. I've pulled in Ssra, Lower Chardok, Karnor's Basement, the Hole and various other places where most folks would want a FD class to pull.<br>
<br>
But PoP has ruined it for me. First off, pulling more than one mob is not efficient, and can be a disaster, depending on how your group is set for dealing with the add. Pulling three of anything in PoP without serious crowd control is wipe city. The generally huge aggro and assist ranges almost guarantee that you will get more than one. <br>
<br>
Combine this with the fact that it suddenly seems like half the classes in the game can pull without getting adds, and I find myself feeling like I'm chained to a post near the cleric - no, wait, the cleric is out there pacifying mobs and possibly pulling as well! Bards pull, Rangers pull, Monks pull, Enchanters pull, Shadow Knights pull, Clerics pull, Necros pull. Hell, give us a little more &quot;Caster balancing&quot; and Mage's pets will probably be pulling.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Why is it that the more I play this game, the less I get to do?<br>
<br>
